CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 16, 1946, pg. 15, reads: "BEAUTY AND LEARNING - Lovely Clara Itsue Funasaki gets her first comprehensive view of Pittsburgh from a vantage point on the University of Pittsburgh campus with the Cathedral of Learning as backdrop. Miss Funasaki hails from Honolulu where she was graduated from the University of Hawaii.  She is graduate student in School of Applied Science and plans a career as a psychiatric social worker in the Paradise Isles of the Pacific. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Clara Itsue Funasaki wearing suit with tied belt at waist, and Vivian Davidson Hewitt, wearing dress with squiggle and musical note pattern, seated on hillside with University of Pittsburgh and Cathedral of Learning in background, Oakland
